So, the nairobi assembly speaker Beatrice Elachi has ruled out any possibility of debating the suitability of governor mike Sonko's nominee for deputy, before mid February, when the house resumes. Tonight, KTN political reporter Murimi Mwangi paints a picture of the capital county's leadership crisis, and explains why Sonko stares at a tough week, as he appears to get back in court, with the director of public prosecutions hel bent on vetoing the governor's nomination.